entry.summary:
You can think of this like fetch() or curl but entirely in SQL: select request_url, response_status, response_headers from http_get('http://httpbin.org/get');
The cool thing is you can save everything from the request: status code, headers, the body (of course), timestamps, and more. Great for archiving! -- initialize a table create table snapshots as select * from http_get('https://changelog.com');
-- To add more rows later on insert into snapshots select * from http_get('https://changelog.com');
